text: Limnonectes selatan is a species of fanged frogs in the family Dicroglossidae. It is endemic to peninsular Malaysia, in the states of Pahang and Selangor. ==References== * Matsui, Belabut & Ahmad, 2014 : Two new species of fanged frogs from Peninsular Malaysia (Anura: Dicroglossidae) Zootaxa, , . *http://research.amnh.org/vz/herpetology/amphibia/Amphibia/Anura/Dicroglossidae/Dicroglossinae/Limnonectes/Limnonectes- selatan Category:Limnonectes Category:Amphibians of Malaysia Category:Frogs of Asia Category:Amphibians described in 2014
title: Limnonectes selatan
